@node Architecture
@chapter Architecture

@menu
* Two-layer boundary::
* Shared contract::
@end menu

@node Two-layer boundary
@section Two-layer boundary

Eve is deliberately split into two independent layers:

@itemize
@item
@strong{The Emacs package} (@samp{eve.el}) owns the user interface: major mode,
interactive editing commands, playback integration, asynchronous process
launching, and parsing of CLI output.  It does not implement media-processing
logic.

@item
@strong{The CLI} (@samp{cli/}, Python) owns all media processing: manifest generation,
denoise orchestration, filler policy, timeline construction, and FFmpeg
invocation.  It does not embed Emacs-specific behaviour.
@end itemize

This boundary means the CLI can be used standalone (e.g. in CI pipelines) and
the Emacs package can evolve independently.

@node Shared contract
@section Shared contract

The two layers communicate through:

@itemize
@item
@strong{TJM files on disk} — the @samp{.tjm.json} format defined in @samp{docs/tjm-spec.md}.
@item
@strong{Machine-readable JSON output} — the CLI emits structured JSON when called
with @samp{--json}; the Emacs package parses it.
@item
@strong{Stable exit codes} — 0 for success, non-zero for failure.
@end itemize

